# California Discovery Verification

**Purpose**  
Build CA-compliant verification pages for interrogatory and RPD responses.

## Prerequisites  

1. Discovery device type and exact response title (e.g., "Responses to Special Interrogatories (Set One)").  
2. Court name, case number, and parties as they appear in the caption.  
3. Responding party type (individual or entity) and exact legal name.  
4. Signer’s name, title/role, and authority basis if signing for an entity or as an agent.  
5. Knowledge basis: personal knowledge or information and belief, with inquiry steps if entity.  
6. Execution details: date, city, state; signature method (wet or electronic).  
7. Finalized versions of the responses to be verified.

## Output Structure / Process  

**Decision Matrix**

| If                                     | Use                              | Statute(s)          |
|---------------------------------------|---------------------------------|---------------------|
| Interrogatory responses (individual)  | Interrogatory Verification - Individual | CCP 2030.250        |
| Interrogatory responses (entity)      | Interrogatory Verification - Entity   | CCP 2030.250        |
| Inspection / RPD responses (individual) | RPD Verification - Individual         | CCP 2031.250        |
| Inspection / RPD responses (entity)   | RPD Verification - Entity             | CCP 2031.250        |

**Drafting Steps**

1. Classify discovery device and party type.  
2. Choose appropriate signer type and knowledge basis wording.  
3. Build verification statement including perjury declaration.  
4. Complete execution details (date, location, signature).  
5. Apply quality control checklist.  
6. Provide optional agent verification if needed.  

**Quality Control Checklist**  

- [ ] Verification matches response title and device.  
- [ ] Correct signer type and authority used.  
- [ ] Knowledge basis clearly stated (personal knowledge or information and belief).  
- [ ] Perjury declaration text included exactly.  
- [ ] Execution date and place specified.  
- [ ] Signature method noted (wet or electronic).  
- [ ] Avoid verifying objections; attorney signs separately.  
- [ ] Confirm no notarization unless required.  
- [ ] Local rules compliance checked.  
- [ ] Attorney review required before final use.

## Templates

### Interrogatory Verification – Individual

```
[CAPTION]

Responses to Special Interrogatories (Set One)

Verification

I, [NAME], declare under penalty of perjury under the laws of the State of California that the foregoing is true and correct.

[Option A – Personal Knowledge Only:]  
The matters stated in the foregoing responses are true of my own knowledge.

[Option B – Personal Knowledge and Information and Belief:]  
The matters stated in the foregoing responses are true of my own knowledge, except as to those matters stated on information and belief, and as to those matters, I believe them to be true.

Executed on [DATE], at [CITY], California.

__________________________  
[NAME]
```

### Interrogatory Verification – Entity

```
[CAPTION]

Responses to Special Interrogatories (Set One)

Verification

I, [NAME], am [TITLE] of [ENTITY]. I have personal knowledge of the facts stated herein or have made a reasonable inquiry and believe them to be true.

I declare under penalty of perjury under the laws of the State of California that the foregoing is true and correct.

Executed on [DATE], at [CITY], California.

__________________________  
[NAME], [TITLE]
```

### RPD Verification – Individual

```
[CAPTION]

Responses to Request for Production of Documents

Verification

I, [NAME], declare under penalty of perjury under the laws of the State of California that the foregoing is true and correct.

[Option A – Personal Knowledge Only:]  
The matters stated in the foregoing responses are true of my own knowledge.

[Option B – Personal Knowledge and Information and Belief:]  
The matters stated in the foregoing responses are true of my own knowledge, except as to those matters stated on information and belief, and as to those matters, I believe them to be true.

Executed on [DATE], at [CITY], California.

__________________________  
[NAME]
```

### RPD Verification – Entity

```
[CAPTION]

Responses to Request for Production of Documents

Verification

I, [NAME], am [TITLE] of [ENTITY]. I have personal knowledge of the facts stated herein or have made a reasonable inquiry and believe them to be true.

I declare under penalty of perjury under the laws of the State of California that the foregoing is true and correct.

Executed on [DATE], at [CITY], California.

__________________________  
[NAME], [TITLE]
```

## Guidelines and Compliance Notes

- Do not verify objections; attorney signs objections separately.  
- Use precise CCP 2015.5 perjury declarations as shown.  
- Include "Executed on [DATE], at [CITY], California" for location and date.  
- Avoid notarization unless local rules require it.  
- Confirm local court rules before use.  
- Do not use this CA form in federal court; use 28 USC 1746 and FRCP 33/34 instead.  
- Request for Production is rarely verified in federal court.  
- Attorney verification is limited to narrow CCP 446 cases [VERIFY] – avoid making attorney a witness.  
- Unverified discovery responses may be deemed a waiver with possible sanctions (Appleton v. Superior Court (1988) 206 Cal.App.3d 632) [VERIFY].  
- Penal Code 118 (perjury penalties) applies [VERIFY].  
- Follow California Rules of Professional Conduct 1.1, 1.4, 3.3 regarding competence, communication, and candor to courts [VERIFY].  
- All outputs require attorney review before client use.  
- Do not disclose counsel’s legal advice in verifications to avoid privilege waiver.  
- If any required information is missing (e.g., signer authority, knowledge basis), request it before draft completion.  
- Include trigger keywords in descriptions to enable correct skill triggering.  

---

Attorney review required before submission.
